.\" termin.al-name: open
.\" termin.al-usage: open [--split horizontal|vertical] <target>
.\" termin.al-summary: Open virtual content inline or in a split viewer pane.
.TH OPEN 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
open \- Open virtual content inline or in a split viewer pane.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
open [--split horizontal|vertical] <target>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Opens a virtual document or collection in a viewer. A split disposition requests a new pane without changing how the target is resolved.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --split horizontal
Open the target in a new horizontal split.
.TP
.B --split vertical
Open the target in a new vertical split.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ open about.md
$ open --split vertical projects
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
help(1), man(1)
